{"name": "Access Florida DCF-Local Office", "alternate_name": "", "description": "How do I apply?
At one of the Florida Department of Children and Families community partners. A listing of community partners can be found online at: https://myaccess.myflfamilies.com/
At a Florida Department of Children and Families customer service center.
Complete a paper application by downloading and printing form here. The completed paper application can be mailed to ACCESS Central Mail Center, P.O. Box 1770, Ocala, FL, 34478-1770, or it can be faxed or hand-delivered to a customer service center 
The quickest way is to Apply for Benefits online. https://myaccess.myflfamilies.com/
Florida Department of Children and Families offers individuals and families with children assistance with filling out applications for government programs in Florida.
This program provides assistance with:
- Apply for American Citizenship
- Employment Authorization
- Permanent Resident
- Notary Letters
- Translations
- Medicare Saving Program (QMB)
- Food Assistance (food stamps)
- Temporary Cash Assistance
- Medicaid
